              "dialogue": "Let me walk you through placing these fractions. First, 6/4 means six fourths. We count six intervals from 0: one, two, three, four gets us to 1, then five, six lands us at 6/4. Next, 7/4 means seven fourths. Count seven intervals from 0, which takes us one more interval past 6/4. Finally, 8/4 means eight fourths. Count eight intervals from 0, and we land at 2. That's how we place fractions past 1 - the numerator tells us how many fourths to count from zero."
